In the *JIRA Import Wizard* screen, a link to use the *Backup manager* redirects to the below and receives a 404:
{code:java}
https://mysite.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/ondemandbackupmanager/admin
{code}
Whereas the Backup manager link in the left hand menu points to:
{code:java}
https://mysite.atlassian.net/secure/admin/CloudExport.jspa
{code}
 

Link:

!image-2017-05-31-13-47-21-858.png!

h3. Summary

The many transitions between workflow have conditions to limit their accessibility by,
 "Only users in project role ... can execute this transition"
 where an example may be
 "Only users in project role IT , Senior Administrators can execute this transition".
 This has been working fine until all selected roles have dropped off from all such workflow transitions simultaneously across ALL workflows.
 Now all conditions users can see are simply "Only users in project role can execute this transition" (i.e. empty and all roles have been "de-selected" when you edit that condition).
h3. Environment

 
|*Version*|1000.990.2|
|*Build Number*|100044|
|*Build Date*|Fri May 19 00:00:00 AEST 2017|
|*Build Revision*|9546d2018b6f5c78616b384ee4af032322b8c504|
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # The bug affects all the issues and all the users in all the projects.
 # You can have a transition that uses several roles "User is In any role" condition, the condition automatically fails so the transition can not be performed by user.
 # This is a common scenario 

 - Only users in project roles *A, B, C* can execute this transition.
Then the bug happened and it started looking like
 - Only users in project role *, , ,* can execute this transition.
So the condition could not be passed and the transition could not be
executed.
 - Commonly occurs with customers using Jira Suite Utilities

h3. Expected Results

Selected roles for these transitions should have dropped and transitions between workflow 
